radiographic_examinations.findings: Markedly immature brain with hyperintensity of the white matter, enlarged lateral ventricles, and almost complete agyria. Presence of paraventricular cysts, a small smooth cerebellum, and large pericerebral spaces.
Markedly attenuated gyri and subependymal cysts.
Micromelia, polyhydramnios, large lateral brain ventricles with a left frontal paraventricular cyst, and dilatation of cerebral posterior fossa.
